.front-content
  h1(style="margin-top:2em"): center
    a(href="https://mellowpine.com/cnc/buildbotics-cnc-controller-review/",
      target="_blank") Read an independent product review.

  section
    h1 The Buildbotics CNC Machine Controller
    center
      img(src="images/buildbotics_with_gamepad_and_steppers.png",
        alt="Buildbotics CNC machine controller with gamepad and stepper " +
        "motors")
    p.
      The Buildbotics controller is a fully enclosed, smart CNC machine
      controller with built-in Web interface and advanced GCode processor.
      It can drive up to 4 stepper motors and many different tools such as
      a CNC spindle, LASER cutter or plasma torch.

    p You can #[a(href="/store") buy it now in our store].

  section
    center
      h2 Frontpanel
      img(src="images/buildbotics_controller_frontpanel.png",
        alt="A diagram of the Buildbotics CNC controller frontpanel")
    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Backpanel
      img(src="images/buildbotics_controller_backpanel_connections.png",
        alt="A diagram of the Buildbotics CNC controller backpanel connections")
    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Main I/O Breakout
      img(src="images/buildbotics_io_breakout_diagram.png",
        alt="A diagram of the Buildbotics CNC controller io breakout box")
    p.
      Connect limit switches, Z-axis probing, PWM spindle control, RS-485
      spindle control, and e-stop switches easily via the included 25-pin
      I/O breakout board using simple screw terminals.

    p Check out the #[a(href="/io-breakout") pin-out diagram].
    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Auxiliary I/O Breakout
      img(src="images/buildbotics_aux_breakout_diagram.png",
        alt="A diagram of the Buildbotics CNC controller auxiliary breakout")
    p.
      Connect step and direction signals to external motor drivers to use
      closed-loop steppers or even servo motors with the Buildbotics controller.

    p.
      Use the 0-10v output to control analog spindles.

    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Included USB Gamepad
      img(src="images/buildbotics_gamepad_controls.png",
        alt="Buildbotics CNC Gamepad controller function diagram")
      p.
        Setup up cuts with ease and agility using the included gamepad.
    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Included Cables
      img(src="images/cables.png", alt="Included Buildbotics cables")
    p.
      The Buildbotics controller comes with the following time saving
      pre-made cables:
    ul
      li 4 x 10 foot (3 meter) Motor cables
      li 1 x 4 foot (1.2 meter) Power cable
    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Optional USB Web Camera
      img(src="images/buildbotics_web_with_camera.png", alt="Screenshot of " +
        "buildbotics Web interface with video with USB camera")
    p.
      With the optional USB camera you can keep an eye on your CNC from
      anywhere using a Web browser or smartphone.  Add it to your controller
      package by selecting the option on #[a(href="/store") our store].
    .clear

  section
    center
      h2 Power Supply Options
      img(src="images/power_supplies.png",
        alt="Two types of MeanWell power supply")
    p.
      Connect any power supply which outputs 24v to 48v DC with at least 6A
      using the included power cable select one of our bundled power supply
      options #[a(href="/store") on our store].
    .clear

  section
    h2 Built-in Stepper Drivers
    .img-left
      img(src="images/steppers2.png", alt="Three different stepper motors")
    ul
      li 4 motor driver channels
      li Up to 6A per channel
      li 24v to 48v DC
      li Up to 256 microstepping
      li Smooth S-curve acceleration
      li Step rates up to 250k/sec per channel.

    p.
      Drive most NEMA 17, NEMA 23 and NEMA 34 motors. Preliminary support for
      4th axis as a rotary axis. The fourth driver can be synchronized to drive
      a single axis with two motors.  Here's a list of some
      #[a(href="/recommended-motors") motors we recommend].
    .clear

  section
    h2 S-Curve Acceleration
    p.
      S-Curve acceleration is an advanced motion planning algorithm which
      smooths out CNC movement.  Most CNC controllers use trapezoidal
      acceleration which is much simpler but results in jerky movement that
      produces rough cuts and increases wear and tear on both tools and the CNC
      machine itself.
    img(src="images/scurve.png", width="600"
      alt="A graph of trapezodial vs S-Curve acceleration profiles")
    .clear

  section
    h2 Awesome Technical Support
    p.
      Get a hold of #[b a real person] when you need to. We provide technical
      support by #[a(href="mailto:info@buildbotics.com") email], phone or via
      #[a(href="//forum.buildbotics.com/") the Buildbotics forum].

    p.
      Check out #[a(href="store/#product-reviews", target="_blank") our reviews]
      to see just how much our customers love our technical support.
    .clear

  section
    h2 Have questions?
    p.
      Email
      (#[a(href="mailto:info@buildbotics.com") info@buildbotics.com]) or call
      us (707-559-8539).  We are happy to help.
    .clear

